    <bioghist>
      <head>Historical Note</head>
      <p>A Christian Connection church was gathered in 1834 in Providence, Rhode Island. By 1841,
        the church had a building on Pawtuxet street and was known as the Pawtuxet Street Christian
        Church. Around 1871, the church moved to a new building on Broad Street and was thereafter
        known as the Broad Street Christian Church.</p>
      <p>The Elmwood Congregational Church, built along Elmwood Avenue, was gathered in 1851 in
        Cranston, Rhode Island, before moving a short distance North to Providence in 1854. The
        church reformed as the Elmwood Temple Congregational Church in 1895.</p>
      <p>In 1912, the Broad Street Christian Church and the Elmwood Congregational Church merged to
        form the Elmwood Christian Church. The Broad Street church building was sold and the money
        was used to build a new church building along Elmwood Avenue. The new building was an
        English Tudor Revival-style building designed by local architect Gorham Henshaw and
        construction on the building was completed in 1915. At first, the Elmwood Christian Church
        was solely a part of the Christian denomination, but by 1934, after the 1931 merger of the
        Christian and Congregational denominations, the church identified itself as
        "Congregational-Christian." The church closed between 1954 and 1955. The building has
        remained a church ever since, first serving as a home to a Presbyterian congregation, then
        as a home for the Providence Assembly of God, and now as the home for the Impact Center
        Providence church.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>This collection contains the records of Elwood Christian Church, In Providence, Rhode
        Island, and the two churches that merged to form it: The Broad Street Christian Church and
        the Elwood Temple Congregational Church. The collection includes vital membership records,
        church records and meeting minutes, legal documents, a pew plan, programs, and
        clippings.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement>
      <head>Arrangement</head>
      <p>This collection has been arranged into the three series listed below. Materials within each
        series have been arranged into chronological order by start date.</p>
      <p><emph render="bold">Series 1:</emph> Broad Street Christian Church records, 1834-1882</p>
      <p><emph render="bold">Series 2:</emph> Elmwood Temple Congregational Church records,
        1895-1912</p>
      <p><emph render="bold">Series 3:</emph> Elmwood Christian Church records, 1912-1955</p>
    </arrangement>
